trans-unit.source: Matches a URL request to a defined route.
The <xref:System.Web.Routing.UrlRoutingModule> class matches an HTTP request to a route in an ASP.NET application.

The module iterates through all the routes in the <xref:System.Web.Routing.UrlRoutingModule.RouteCollection%2A> property and searches for a route that has a URL pattern that matches the format of the HTTP request.
When the module finds a matching route, it retrieves the <xref:System.Web.Routing.IRouteHandler> object for that route.
From the route handler, the module gets an <xref:System.Web.IHttpHandler> object and uses that as the HTTP handler for the current request.
Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.Web.Routing.UrlRoutingModule"></xref> class.
Disposes of the resources (other than memory) that are used by the module.
Initializes a module and prepares it to handle requests.

The <xref:System.Web.Routing.UrlRoutingModule.PostMapRequestHandler%2A> method is called when the <xref:System.Web.HttpApplication.PostMapRequestHandler> event is raised.

The <xref href="System.Web.Routing.RouteData.RouteHandler"></xref> property for the route is `null`.
Matches the HTTP request to a route, retrieves the handler for that route, and sets the handler as the HTTP handler for the current request.
